Within minutes of the crash, emergency calls poured on Salveo&#39;s local
lines.  Atlantis fire crews had already redeployed to the scene.

&quot;At least we know where it is...&quot; he said, feeling the slow pang of
what humans would call a headache.

&quot;Perseus, you&#39;l be happy to know our shuttle&#39;s back,&quot; he said.
&quot;Unfortunately they decided to crash it into the emergency landing
site...&quot;

&quot;What is going on with Rodimus?&quot;

&quot;Nothing, no one will talk.  I think we need to investigate....&quot;

&quot;Right.  Try to get ahold of Doc or Guardia.  We need to know their
status.&quot;  he said.  &quot;Dispatch a team to welcome our little run-aways
as well...&quot;

&quot;It would sure be nice to have people to dispatch....Salveo out...&quot;

